                  <interp inst="t18270913-138-crimeloc793" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-138-off791 t18270913-138-crimeloc793"></join>. On the 24th of July, on coming home, between seven and eight o'clock, I heard our drying ground had been robbed. I applied to the constable, and next day I saw a pawnbroker, who described a person to me. I saw the prisoner carrying a bundle on the road, and had him secured, and taken into a public-house; I asked what he had in the bundle; he said two shirts; I opened them, and said they were mine. I had the fellow shirt on - I never saw him before.</p>
